Sentencas: Synergy effects of mixing Pr2NiO4 and La(Ba)CoO3 on cathodic performance were investigated using a LaGaO3-based oxide electrolyte.
Titulo: Synergy effects of Pr1.91 Ni0.71CU0.24Ga0.05O4 and Ba0.5La0.5CoO3 composite on cathodic activity for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: It was observed that cathodic overpotential could be suppressed significantly by mixing Pr2NiO4 with La(Ba)CoO3 base oxide, in spite of a decrease in the electrical conductivity.
Titulo: Synergy effects of Pr1.91 Ni0.71CU0.24Ga0.05O4 and Ba0.5La0.5CoO3 composite on cathodic activity for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Because LaCoO3-doped with Ba shows high oxygen dissociation activity and Pr2NiO4 shows high oxide ion and hole conductivity, the active sites for oxygen dissociation could be extended in three dimensions.
Titulo: Synergy effects of Pr1.91 Ni0.71CU0.24Ga0.05O4 and Ba0.5La0.5CoO3 composite on cathodic activity for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In response to the improved number of active sites, diffusion overpotential was decreased significantly by mixing Pr2NiO4-based oxide with LaCoO3-based oxide.
Titulo: Synergy effects of Pr1.91 Ni0.71CU0.24Ga0.05O4 and Ba0.5La0.5CoO3 composite on cathodic activity for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of 117 mW cm(-2) was achieved at temperatures as low as 673 K using a LaGaO3 thin film electrolyte (5-mu m thick) and a composite oxide of Pr2NiO4-La(Ba)CoO3 cathode.
Titulo: Synergy effects of Pr1.91 Ni0.71CU0.24Ga0.05O4 and Ba0.5La0.5CoO3 composite on cathodic activity for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
